} ""}]}]}},{"id":"931ac237-92fb-4779-be9e-cc414925ff56","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"To rewrite the `createAssessment` method using the `@Builder` annotation from Lombok, you can utilize the builder pattern provided by Lombok to construct the `Assessment` object. This approach makes the code more readable and flexible. Here's how you can refactor the `createAssessment` method:

```java
@Override
public AssessmentResponse createAssessment(CreateAssessmentRequest request) {
 Assessment assessment = Assessment.builder()
 .creatorId(request.getCreatorId())
 .title(request.getTitle())
 .description(request.getDescription())
 .questionIds(new ArrayList<>())
 .timerDuration(request.getTimerDuration())
 .isOptionsRandomize(request.isRandomizeOptions())
 .isQuestionsRandomize(request.isRandomizeQuestions())
 .createdAt(LocalDateTime.now())
 .updatedAt(LocalDateTime.now())
 .build();

 Assessment savedAssessment = assessmentRepo.save(assessment);
 return convertToResponse(savedAssessment);
}
```

### Explanation:

- **Builder Pattern**: The `@Builder` annotation in Lombok generates a builder class for the `Assessment` class. This allows you to construct an `Assessment` object using a fluent API.
- **Fluent API**: The builder pattern provides a more readable and maintainable way to construct objects, especially when dealing with many parameters.
- **Null Handling**: The `id` field is not set during the build process since it is typically generated by the database upon saving.

This refactoring assumes that the `Assessment` class is annotated with `@Builder`, as shown in the retrieved chunk. If the `@Builder` annotation is not present, you need to add it to the `Assessment` class definition."}],"context":{"attachedFiles":[{"path":"src\main\java\assessment\manager\dtos\responses\AssessmentListResponse.java","fsPath":"C:/Users/DELL/Desktop/Assessment_Management_Sysytem/Backend/src/main/java/assessment/manager/dtos/responses/AssessmentListResponse.java"}],"currentFile":{"path":"src\main\java\assessment\manager\services\implementations\AssessmentServiceImpl.java","fsPath":"C:\Users\DELL\Desktop\Assessment_Management_Sysytem\Backend\src\main\java\assessment\manager\services\implementations\AssessmentServiceImpl.java","sources":["opened_tab"],"content":"package assessment.manager.services.implementations;

